            ],
            "result": {
              "type": "singleLineText"
            }
          },
          "id": "fldQZqvqDTpxOcNCl",
          "name": "Key Results Text",
          "description": "Displays the data on the key results from the linked Objectives as a single string."
        },
        {
          "type": "aiText",
          "options": {
            "referencedFieldIds": [
              "fldjaklC9ACZAbFK7",
              "fldQZqvqDTpxOcNCl"
            ],
            "prompt": [
              "Objective: ",
              {
                "field": {
                  "fieldId": "fldjaklC9ACZAbFK7"
                }
              },
              "\nKey Results associated with Objective: ",
              {
                "field": {
                  "fieldId": "fldQZqvqDTpxOcNCl"
                }
              },
              "\n\n🧠 Singular OKR Evaluation Prompt – Final Version (With Scoring)\n✅ OKR Evaluation Summary – Mandatory Scoring Header\n🔢 Total Score: __/100%\nOnly OKRs scoring 90%+ are eligible for execution, roadmap linkage, or leadership presentation.\n   Evaluation Category Max Score Your Score Comment Summary     🎯 Objective = Business Outcome 20     📏 KRs = Measurable & Time-bound 25     ❌ Binary KRs ≤ 10% 10     🔗 Project ↔ KR Linkage = Full 25     📣 Stakeholder Story is Clear 20     Total 100     🔍 Evaluator Verdict\n🟩 Proceed (≥90%)\n 🟨 Needs Refinement (80–89%)\n 🟥 Rebuild (≤79%)\n🔻 PHASE 1: OBJECTIVE KILL-TEST\nAsk:\nDoes it describe a business outcome (not a task or tool)?\nIs it timeboxed with a clear lever, audience, and strategic anchor?\nWould leadership or a client nod and say, “Yes, that’s what matters”?\n✅ Use Format:\n[Verb] + [Lever] + [Audience] + [Change] by [Date]\n❌ Reject If:\nIt mentions tools/methods (e.g., “Launch chatbot”)\nHas no deadline or vague verbs (“Optimize,” “Improve”)\nSounds like a Jira epic, not a strategic goal\n📏 PHASE 2: KEY RESULT INTEGRITY\nAsk:\nAre KRs quantified, specific, and outcome-based?\nAre they free of binary, milestone, or task phrasing?\nDo they show actual business impact (cost, revenue, time, quality)?\n✅ Use Format:\n[Metric] from [Baseline] to [Target] by [Date]\n❌ Watch For:\n\"Launch X\", \"Complete Y\", \"Implement Z\"\nVanity metrics (e.g., open rates, click rates without context)\nNon-KPI language that leadership wouldn't care about\n🛠 PHASE 3: PROJECT–KR FIT CHECK\nAsk:\nDoes each project directly support a KR?\nIs it scoped for 90-day execution with a clear DRI?\nDoes it combine delivery, enablement, and feedback?\n✅ Use Format:\n[Verb] + [Outcome] + [KR Impact]\n❌ Disqualify If:\nIt’s an activity without outcome (e.g., “research,” “align”)\nIt lacks a KR link or named owner\nIt's duplicated work from a stale backlog\n🔗 PHASE 4: LOGIC CHAIN INTEGRITY\nAsk:\nIf we complete the Projects, do the KRs move?\nIf all KRs go green, does the Objective clearly land?\nAre there orphaned Projects or unsupported KRs?\n✅ Use linkage map or dashboard to visualize integrity\n ❌ Cut anything that fails causal logic\n🗣 PHASE 5: EXECUTIVE STORYTELLING CHECK\nAsk:\nCan the OKR set be summarized in one business sentence?\n✅ Use Format:\n“We’re helping [Team/Client] achieve [Strategic Goal] by [Projects], proven by [KRs] by [Date].”\n❌ Rework If:\nIt's loaded with tech jargon\nLeadership can't repeat it after hearing it once\nIt doesn't connect to margin, revenue, or strategic positioning\n📊 PHASE 6: FINAL QUALITY SCORECARD\n(Reused from Header)\n   Evaluation Category Max Score Your Score Comment Summary     🎯 Objective = Business Outcome 20     📏 KRs = Measurable & Time-bound 25     ❌ Binary KRs ≤ 10% 10     🔗 Project ↔ KR Linkage = Full 25     📣 Stakeholder Story is Clear 20     Total 100     🧩 Key Reminder:\n“Every KR is a contract with reality. Every project is a bet on ROI. If your OKR set doesn’t hold under C-level scrutiny—it’s not ready.”\n\n"
            ]
          },
          "id": "fldsk8iAQvOrYCft9",
          "name": "Health Score"
        },
        {
          "type": "aiText",
          "options": {
            "referencedFieldIds": [
              "fldsk8iAQvOrYCft9"
            ],
            "prompt": [
              "extract the percentage grade of the health score of ",
              {
                "field": {
                  "fieldId": "fldsk8iAQvOrYCft9"
                }
              },
              "and set as a numerical percentage only \n"
            ]
          },
          "id": "flduZIv8pC8t28TJb",
          "name": "Health Grade"
        },
        {
          "type": "formula",
          "options": {
            "isValid": true,
            "formula": "{flduZIv8pC8t28TJb}",
            "referencedFieldIds": [
              "flduZIv8pC8t28TJb"
