        {
          "type": "aiText",
          "options": {
            "referencedFieldIds": [
              "fldJI7UdzncMXrgDP",
              "fldZaG3dLRR23DXeK",
              "fldHNreR04hmHzMsG",
              "fldBifg9QIowMbTfw"
            ],
            "prompt": [
              "Generate an executive summary for the Sprint [Sprint Name] using the following stories. The response should be client value-focused, using key deliverables in bullet points. Each deliverable should end with the talent name(s) involved in parentheses. Separate administrative tasks (Scrum Master and Product Owner)\nInclude these Sprint details at the start:\n\t•\t",
              {
                "field": {
                  "fieldId": "fldJI7UdzncMXrgDP"
                }
              },
              "\nSprint Name\n ",
              {
                "field": {
                  "fieldId": "fldJI7UdzncMXrgDP"
                }
              },
              "﻿\t\n•\t",
              {
                "field": {
                  "fieldId": "fldZaG3dLRR23DXeK"
                }
              },
              " SO Date\n•\t",
              {
                "field": {
                  "fieldId": "fldHNreR04hmHzMsG"
                }
              },
              " SF Date\n\n SF DateHere is the list of Stories worked in the sprint\n",
              {
                "field": {
                  "fieldId": "fldBifg9QIowMbTfw"
                }
              },
              "\nThe structure should be:\n\t1.\tSprint name.\n\t2.\tKey Deliverables grouped by impact.\n\t3.\tPotential KPIs affected.\n\t4.\tAdministrative tasks at the end.\n\nReplace the (Talent or talents: [just one name by talent]) with the name of the person who collaborated in the completion of the Key Deliverable.\nThe list of Key Deliverables should be the list of TLDRs, so it can be observed who participated in completing a common goal, and not just a list without grouping.\n\nCreate the Potential KPIs Impacted base on what's worked on the Stories and List it.\n\nTemplate Example:\n\n[Sprint Name]\nPotential KPIs Impacted:\n1. [Create list of KPI's]\n\nKey Deliverables:\n1. [Create list of Key Deliverables] (Talent or talents how participated in this Key, use one name not full names).\n\nAdministrative Tasks:\n1.\t[Scrum Master Name] coordinated sprint activities and ensured smooth collaboration across the teams.\n2.\t[Product Owner Name] oversaw product vision alignment and backlog prioritization.\n"
            ]
          },
          "id": "fldmWLqn5lvFlSoJP",
          "name": "Singular Stories Sprint Order TLDR AI"
        },
        {
          "type": "rating",
          "options": {
            "icon": "star",
            "max": 10,
            "color": "yellowBright"
          },
          "id": "fldCxNooiMPZTRlKG",
          "name": "Credibility Scrum Master to Client"
        },
        {
          "type": "formula",
          "options": {
            "isValid": true,
            "formula": "SWITCH(\n  {fldCxNooiMPZTRlKG},\n  1, \"Poor: Credibility is deficient. The client provides no details about their goals and specific needs for the project's success, greatly hindering proper planning and execution.\",\n  2, \"Very Low: Credibility is very low. The client provides very few details about their goals and specific needs for the project's success, but the information is insufficient and leaves significant gaps affecting overall understanding.\",\n  3, \"Low: Credibility is low. The client provides some details about their goals and specific needs for the project's success, which does not allow for reasonable planning and execution.\",\n  4, \"Below Average: Credibility is unacceptable. The client does not provide clear and precise details about their goals and specific needs for the project's success.\",\n  5, \"Average: Credibility is acceptable. The client provides an average amount of details about their goals and specific needs for the project's success, enabling precise and focused planning and execution.\",\n  6, \"Satisfactory: Credibility is very good. The client provides an exceptional amount of details about their goals and specific needs for the project's success, facilitating highly effective and seamless planning and execution.\",\n  7, \"Moderately High: Credibility is excellent. The client offers a deep and comprehensive understanding of their goals and specific needs for the project's success, enabling exceptional planning and execution with absolute clarity.\",\n  8, \"High: Credibility is high. The client provides detailed and exhaustive documentation of their goals and specific needs for the project's success, demonstrating an exceptional level of commitment and clarity in communication.\",\n  9, \"Very High: Credibility is very high. The client goes above and beyond by providing extremely detailed and precise information about their goals and specific needs for the project's success, demonstrating an extraordinary level of trust and transparency in the working relationship.\",\n  10, \"Exceptional: Credibility is exceptionally high. The client sets an exceptional standard by providing impeccable and comprehensive understanding of their goals and specific needs for the project's success, evidencing unwavering commitment and exceptionally clear and precise communication.\",\n  \"The score is out of range or not a number\"\n)",
            "referencedFieldIds": [
              "fldCxNooiMPZTRlKG"
            ],
            "result": {
              "type": "singleLineText"
            }
          },
