              "fldQJ2n716BpXKAmU",
              "fldOmptEdGAYa0bWl"
            ],
            "prompt": [
              "You are a QA Performance Analyst. Based on Airtable data — including:\nSprint Name: ",
              {
                "field": {
                  "fieldId": "fldJI7UdzncMXrgDP"
                }
              },
              "\nOut of a total of:  ",
              {
                "field": {
                  "fieldId": "fldAKpqrVjuhlJLym"
                }
              },
              "\nCompleted: ",
              {
                "field": {
                  "fieldId": "fldw2zym5taxmYow0"
                }
              },
              "\nWith the comments:  ",
              {
                "field": {
                  "fieldId": "fldg9KuPpJENlpAd4"
                }
              },
              "\nLeft pending at the end of this sprint: ",
              {
                "field": {
                  "fieldId": "fldbua3u4LERs1gg8"
                }
              },
              "\nWith the comments: ",
              {
                "field": {
                  "fieldId": "fldzYmXDrX9IkjgmP"
                }
              },
              "\nSprint Order ",
              {
                "field": {
                  "fieldId": "fldZaG3dLRR23DXeK"
                }
              },
              "\nSprint finish: ",
              {
                "field": {
                  "fieldId": "fldHNreR04hmHzMsG"
                }
              },
              "\nStories Reviewed: ",
              {
                "field": {
                  "fieldId": "fldQJ2n716BpXKAmU"
                }
              },
              "\nCount Stories Review By QA: \n",
              {
                "field": {
                  "fieldId": "fldOmptEdGAYa0bWl"
                }
              },
              "\nGenerate a professional Executive QA Performance Report using the structure below. The report must provide a clear, concise, and insightful summary of QA performance for executive stakeholders.\n\n\nExecutive Summary – QA Performance Report\n\nReport Date: [Insert current date]\nPeriod: Current Sprint ([Sprint Name])\nOverall Status: [Choose one: STABLE / AT RISK / CRITICAL]\n\n\n\nKey Highlights\n\nTotal Issues Raised: [Total QAs Raised]\nIssues Resolved: [Total QAs Completed]\nIssues Pending: [Total QAs Pending]\nCompletion Rate: [% Completed = Completed / Raised]\nSprint End Date: [Sprint Finish Date]\nStories Reviewed by QA: [Count Stories Review By QA]\nIf possible, compare the above values with the previous sprint.\nMention any open critical or high-priority issues based on comments.\n\n\n\nAnalysis & Insights\n\nAssess the QA team’s efficiency and trends in issue handling.\nDescribe changes in completion rate or volume of issues raised.\nMention improvements or delays in resolution time or quality.\nInclude QA feedback from the comments to highlight key blockers, patterns, or testing improvements.\nReflect on collaboration with developers or stakeholders.\n\n\n\nRecommendations\n\nBased on the data, provide at least 3 actionable recommendations, such as:\n\nResource Allocation: Add QA resources if completion rate is below target.\nProcess Enhancements: Improve bug triaging or communication workflows.\nAutomation Opportunities: Use scripts or tools to catch repetitive defects early.\nReview Depth: Increase focus on story reviews if the count is low.\nPreventive Actions: Use unresolved issues as learning points for next sprint.\n\n\nUse an executive-level tone throughout. Highlight what QA achieved, what was left pending, the root causes, and what can be improved. This report must showcase QA’s strategic role in ensuring quality delivery and help leadership make informed decisions.\n\n"
            ]
          },
