            "formula": "SWITCH(\n  {fldsxP7kZJTh59aLL},\n  1, \"Poor: Credibility is minimal. There is a total lack of knowledge and effective application of Scrum methodologies by the Product Owner.\",\n  2, \"Very Low: Credibility is very low. There is limited knowledge and inconsistent applications of Scrum by the Product Owner.\",\n  3, \"Low: Credibility is low. Although there are some basic understandings, the application of Scrum is deficient and requires substantial improvement.\",\n  4, \"Below Average: Credibility is moderate. The Product Owner demonstrates basic knowledge and acceptable application of Scrum, but there are still areas for improvement.\",\n  5, \"Average: Credibility is acceptable. The Product Owner has a general understanding and reasonable application of Scrum, meeting basic expectations.\",\n  6, \"Satisfactory: Credibility is good. The Product Owner demonstrates solid knowledge and consistent application of Scrum, being reliable in most situations.\",\n  7, \"Moderately High: Credibility is very good. The Product Owner consistently exceeds expectations in terms of knowledge and application of Scrum.\",\n  8, \"High: Credibility is excellent. The Product Owner excels in knowledge and application of Scrum, being a reference in the organization.\",\n  9, \"Very High: Credibility is outstanding. The Product Owner demonstrates exceptional knowledge and outstanding application of Scrum, being highly reliable in any situation.\",\n  10, \"Outstanding: Credibility is exceptional. The Product Owner is a Scrum expert, with exceptional knowledge and application that make them trustworthy in any circumstance.\",\n  \"The score is out of range or not a number\"\n)",
