            "formula": "SWITCH(\n  {fldEI7C1m6eA1BlB1},\n  1, \"Poor: Group Thinking is poor. The talent shows extremely limited interaction with the team, lacks value proposition generation, has minimal engagement, and demonstrates no service acts at all.\",\n  2, \"Very Low: Group Thinking is very low. There are very notable deficiencies in the talent's interaction with the team, as well as in value proposition generation. Their level of engagement is limited, and the demonstration of service acts is occasional and insignificant.\",\n  3, \"Low: Group Thinking is low. The talent shows limited interaction with the team and fails to generate acceptable value propositions. They participate regularly, although could be more proactive, and demonstrate some service acts, though inconsistently.\",\n  4, \"Below Average: Group Thinking is acceptable. The talent interacts positively with the team, consistently generating valuable propositions. They actively participate in team activities and regularly demonstrate service acts, contributing to the project's success.\",\n  5, \"Average: Group Thinking is average. The talent has notable interaction with the team, consistently generating high-quality value propositions. They actively participate in all team activities and proactively demonstrate service acts, strengthening team cohesion.\",\n  6, \"Satisfactory: Group Thinking is satisfactory. The talent exceeds expectations by exceptionally interacting with the team, consistently generating innovative and high-impact value propositions. They proactively and enthusiastically participate in all team activities and demonstrate exemplary service acts, serving as a role model for others.\",\n  7, \"Moderately High: Group Thinking is excellent. The talent stands out for their exceptional interaction with the team, continuously generating innovative and high-impact value propositions. They proactively and enthusiastically participate in all team activities and demonstrate outstanding service acts, being a key pillar for the project's success.\",\n  8, \"High: Group Thinking is exceptional. The talent shows exceptional interaction with the team, generating value propositions that significantly transform the project. They proactively and enthusiastically participate in all team activities and demonstrate exceptional service acts, being a positive change agent in the workplace.\",\n  9, \"Very High: Group Thinking is exceptionally high. The talent sets an exceptional standard in their interaction with the team, generating revolutionary value propositions and serving as a catalyst for innovation. They proactively and enthusiastically participate in all team activities and demonstrate exceptional service acts, creating a highly collaborative and successful work environment.\",\n  10, \"Outstanding: Group Thinking is outstanding. The talent exhibits exceptional interaction with the team, consistently generating innovative and high-impact value propositions. They proactively and enthusiastically participate in all team activities and demonstrate exceptional service acts, being an inspiring leader for others.\",\n  \"The score is out of range or not a number\"\n)",
