        {
          "type": "formula",
          "options": {
            "isValid": true,
            "formula": "SWITCH(\n  {fldylRlAbxrUoiBbG},\n  1, \"Poor: Group Thinking is poor. The Product Owner shows a complete lack of initiative to collaborate with the team, share knowledge and expectations, as well as to address team-affecting issues. This results in disconnection and lack of cohesion in the group.\",\n  2, \"Very Low: Group Thinking is very low. There are notable deficiencies in the Product Owner's initiative to collaborate with the team, share knowledge and expectations, as well as to resolve issues. This may lead to a lack of alignment and effectiveness in the team.\",\n  3, \"Low: Group Thinking is low. The Product Owner shows low initiative to collaborate with the team, share knowledge and expectations, as well as to address some issues.\",\n  4, \"Below Average: Group Thinking meets expectations. The Product Owner demonstrates good initiative to closely collaborate with the team, share knowledge and expectations, and address team-affecting issues. This positively contributes to the overall project performance.\",\n  5, \"Average: Group Thinking is good. The Product Owner shows a solid initiative to collaborate with the team, effectively share knowledge and expectations, and promptly address issues. This promotes a strong and efficient teamwork culture.\",\n  6, \"Satisfactory: Group Thinking is very good. The Product Owner exceeds expectations by demonstrating exceptional initiative to closely collaborate with the team, proactively share knowledge and expectations, and effectively and timely address issues. This fosters a highly collaborative and productive work environment.\",\n  7, \"Moderately High: Group Thinking is excellent. The Product Owner excels in the initiative to closely collaborate with the team, exceptionally share knowledge and expectations, and promptly and efficiently address issues. This drives a high level of performance and cohesion in the team.\",\n  8, \"High: Group Thinking is outstanding. The Product Owner exhibits exceptional initiative to promote collaboration within the team, outstandingly share knowledge and expectations, and effectively resolve issues. This creates an exceptionally productive and harmonious work environment.\",\n  9, \"Very High: Group Thinking is exceptional. The Product Owner demonstrates an exceptionally high level of initiative to foster collaboration within the team, exceptionally share knowledge and expectations, and masterfully address issues. This sets an exceptional standard of performance within the team.\",\n  10, \"Outstanding: Group Thinking is exceptionally high. The Product Owner not only exceptionally fulfills all the aforementioned expectations but also sets an exceptionally high standard for promoting group thinking in the workplace, creating a highly effective and cohesive team.\",\n  \"The score is out of range or not a number\"\n)",
