            "formula": "SWITCH(\n  {fldYhO4R6mlrHSrpT},\n  1, \"Poor: Intimacy is deficient. The talent shows very limited commitment to the project and a lack of willingness to maintain healthy relationships with both the team and the client, resulting in significant disconnection.\",\n  2, \"Very Low: Intimacy is very low. There are notable deficiencies in the talent's commitment to the project and their willingness to maintain healthy relationships, creating a noticeable distance in work interactions.\",\n  3, \"Low: Intimacy is low. The talent shows commitment below expectations to the project and reasonable willingness to maintain healthy relationships, although emotional and professional connections can improve.\",\n  4, \"Below Average: Intimacy is acceptable. The talent demonstrates good commitment to the project and a positive willingness to maintain healthy relationships with both the team and the client, establishing significant and constructive connections.\",\n  5, \"Average: Intimacy is good. The talent shows notable commitment to the project and an excellent willingness to maintain healthy relationships, fostering a harmonious and collaborative work environment.\",\n  6, \"Satisfactory: Intimacy is very good. The talent exceeds expectations in terms of commitment to the project and their willingness to maintain healthy relationships, promoting a work culture based on trust and closeness.\",\n  7, \"Moderately High: Intimacy is excellent. The talent excels in commitment to the project and their ability to maintain healthy relationships, establishing deep and trustworthy connections both within the team and with the client.\",\n  8, \"High: Intimacy is outstanding. The talent exhibits exceptional commitment to the project and outstanding ability to maintain healthy relationships, excelling in building strong and meaningful bonds in the work environment.\",\n  9, \"Very High: Intimacy is exceptional. The talent demonstrates exceptional commitment and exceptional ability to maintain healthy relationships, being highly reliable in promoting a collaborative and supportive work culture.\",\n  10, \"Outstanding: Intimacy is exceptionally high. The talent sets an exceptional standard for commitment to the project and the ability to maintain healthy relationships, creating a deeply connected and highly trustworthy work environment with both the team and the client.\"\n)",
