        {
          "type": "formula",
          "options": {
            "isValid": true,
            "formula": "IF(\n  {fldktzcwDudNfkOOg} = \"Client\", \n  SWITCH(\n    {flde3L6JwKi7W5CjD},\n    1, \"Poor: Group thinking is poor. The client shows a complete lack of openness to collaborate and receive value propositions, and does not actively participate in discussions to enhance the project's success.\",\n    2, \"Very Low: Group thinking is very low. The client displays minimal openness to collaborate and is highly reluctant to receive value propositions, significantly limiting the ability to improve the project's success through discussions.\",\n    3, \"Low: Group thinking is low. The client shows some openness to collaborate and receive value propositions, but in a limited manner. They participate minimally in discussions to enhance the project's success.\",\n    4, \"Below Average: Group thinking is below average. Although the client shows some openness to collaborate and receive value propositions, as well as occasional participation in discussions, it is not sufficient to significantly drive the project's success.\",\n    5, \"Average: Group thinking is average. The client demonstrates moderate openness to collaborate and receive value propositions, and occasionally participates in discussions to enhance the project's success, albeit inconsistently.\",\n    6, \"Satisfactory: Group thinking is satisfactory. The client displays acceptable openness to collaborate and receive value propositions, and regularly participates in discussions to enhance the project's success, contributing positively.\",\n    7, \"Moderately High: Group thinking is moderately high. The client exhibits good openness to collaborate and receive value propositions, and actively engages in discussions to enhance the project's success, greatly benefiting its realization.\",\n    8, \"High: Group thinking is high. The client shows strong openness to collaborate and receive value propositions, and enthusiastically participates in discussions to enhance the project's success, significantly driving its progress.\",\n    9, \"Very High: Group thinking is very high. The client demonstrates exceptional openness to collaborate and receive value propositions, and actively and proactively engages in discussions to enhance the project's success, acting as a catalyst for advancement.\",\n    10, \"Outstanding: Group thinking is outstanding. The client displays exceptionally high openness to collaborate and receive value propositions, and participates exceptionally in discussions to enhance the project's success, leading and motivating the team towards excellence.\",\n    BLANK()\n  ), \n  IF(\n    {flde3L6JwKi7W5CjD} = BLANK(), \n    BLANK(),\n    SWITCH(\n      {flde3L6JwKi7W5CjD},\n      1, \"Does not collaborate at all and acts solely in self-interest.\",\n      2, \"Rarely collaborates, prioritizing personal interests.\",\n      3, \"Shows little willingness to collaborate and acts in an individualistic manner.\",\n      4, \"Sometimes collaborates, but prioritizes personal interests over the team's.\",\n      5, \"Has a moderately collaborative attitude, although does not always prioritize the common good.\",\n      6, \"Generally collaborates, though in some situations individual interests are evident.\",\n      7, \"Actively collaborates in most decisions and tends to prioritize team interests.\",\n      8, \"Is collaborative and prioritizes the group's well-being over personal interests.\",\n      9, \"Always collaborates effectively and advocates for group thinking, prioritizing collective well-being.\",\n      10, \"Is an exemplary collaborator, consistently prioritizing team interests and working for the common good.\"\n    )\n  )\n)",
