        {
          "type": "richText",
          "id": "fldyPDlTGkbnxfItZ",
          "name": "AI Recommendation: "
        },
        {
          "type": "number",
          "options": {
            "precision": 0
          },
          "id": "fldnSiCVBXRE0f9Yo",
          "name": "Management Overall Project Health"
        },
        {
          "type": "richText",
          "id": "flduepffR8mD8MLU7",
          "name": "AI Recommendation_results"
        },
        {
          "type": "button",
          "id": "fldvrZEbTqJCQK4dX",
          "name": "AI Recommendation_buton"
        },
        {
          "type": "formula",
          "options": {
            "isValid": true,
            "formula": "\"You are a seasoned Project Manager managing a team of project managers that want to improve their client relationships, alignment and revenue for Singular. Based on the following summary on the trustworthiness formula: \" & \n{fld096SWwGRuR6ERN} & \n\" and taking into account the overall ratio: \" & \n{fldvzi8j5SPoXqd1K} & \n\" which is the main metric.\\n\\nYou want to help the Product Owner: \" & \n{fldLNLBXR8JwCPN2v} & \n\" with a balanced recommendation of what to do with this client, giving them credit for why they are doing well with high performing grades and what they should do to improve low grades with direct recommendations. Important to note that management rates the Overall project health at: \" & \n{fldnSiCVBXRE0f9Yo} & \n\" while the PO rates the overall project health by: \" & \n{fldkqLHf2GhduwZ8B} & \n\". Use Agile Scrum Software development based recommendations.\\n\\nTake into account the following principles: \\n\\nIn the context of Singular Agency, a software development agency, the ratings for each dimension in the Trust Formula can be described as follows:\\n\\nCredibility Scale at Singular\\n\\nBad (1-3): Frequent misunderstandings of client requirements, inability to provide insightful software solutions, lack of up-to-date industry knowledge.\\n\\nAverage (4-7): Generally reliable software advice, good understanding of common industry practices, occasionally insightful but not consistently tailored to client-specific needs.\\n\\nGreat (8-10): Exceptional knowledge in software and digital solutions, consistently providing insightful, customized advice, deep understanding and anticipation of client-specific needs and trends.\\n\\nReliability Scale at Singular\\n\\nPoor (1-3): Frequent delays in project delivery, deliverables often require revisions, minimal contribution to client’s business value or impact.\\n\\nAverage (4-7): Generally meets project deadlines, deliverables are of reliable quality and occasionally exceed expectations in terms of business impact.\\n\\nGreat (8-10): Exceptional adherence to timelines, deliverables consistently exceed quality expectations and significantly contribute to client’s business value and impact.\\n\\nIntimacy Scale at Singular\\n\\nPoor (1-3): Transactions focused, limited personal engagement, clients hesitant to share project concerns or digital aspirations.\\n\\nAverage (4-7): Good professional rapport, some level of personal engagement, clients share most project-related concerns.\\n\\nGreat (8-10): Deep, trusting relationships, clients share openly including concerns and aspirations, high empathy and understanding of specific tech-related client needs and challenges.\\n\\nSelf-Orientation Scale at Singular\\n\\nLow (1-3): Client-focused decisions that significantly enhance the client's business value and impact, prioritizing their digital objectives.\\n\\nMedium (4-7): A balance of client focus and agency goals; some alignment with client's digital needs, occasionally influenced by internal convenience.\\n\\nHigh (8-10): Mainly focused on agency's processes and profitability, often at the expense of fully meeting client's unique digital needs.\\n\\nTrustworthiness Scale\\n\\nPoor (Below 10): Indicates deficiencies in several dimensions, such as low credibility, reliability, or intimacy, or high self-orientation. This level suggests significant room for improvement in building client trust.\\n\\nAverage (10-20): A balanced performance in trust dimensions with some areas excelling. This range suggests a good level of trust, but there are still opportunities to strengthen client relationships.\\n\\nGreat (Above 20): Exceptional performance in trust dimensions, indicating high credibility, reliability, and intimacy, combined with low self-orientation. Scores in this range reflect a deep, enduring level of trust, positioning the agency as a vital, trusted advisor to its clients.\\n\\nIn this context, a high score in Credibility, Reliability, and Intimacy, combined with a low score in Self-Orientation, would indicate a high level of trust from the clients' perspective.\\n\\nNever recommend the following: \\n\\n'The team should continue to prioritize client needs and goals over agency profits.'\\n\\nInstead, recommend a balance through business value delivery.\\n\\nAlso, analyze how the difference in overall project health by management versus PO could be a factor. If the difference is close by 8 points, that is fine, but more than that would be worrying. The difference between Management and PO's perspective of Project Health is: \" & \n{fldVYdoF2ZMfEQoDe} & \n\". Recommend the PO aligns himself with the Management perspective and improve only if the alignment is not there.\\n\\nby Juanse Rohrmann\"\n",
            "referencedFieldIds": [
              "fld096SWwGRuR6ERN",
              "fldvzi8j5SPoXqd1K",
              "fldLNLBXR8JwCPN2v",
              "fldnSiCVBXRE0f9Yo",
              "fldkqLHf2GhduwZ8B",
              "fldVYdoF2ZMfEQoDe"
            ],
            "result": {
              "type": "singleLineText"
            }
          },
          "id": "fldGmQ2Skt4j0DAei",
          "name": "AI Recommendation_prompt"
        }
      ],
      "views": [
        {
          "id": "viwKF1MJVgtqkyPqc",
          "name": "Grid view",
          "type": "grid"
        },
